data.text:
Kylie Ann Minogue, AO, OBE (born 28 May 1968), often known simply as Kylie, is an Australian-British singer, songwriter, actress, and record producer. Having sold 70 million records worldwide, Minogue is the best-selling female Australian artist of all time and has been recognised for reinventing herself in music and fashion, for which she is referred to by the European press as the "Princess of Pop" and a style icon. Her accolades include a Grammy Award, three Brit Awards and 17 ARIA Music Awards...
